ed an exhibition at the John Hansard Gallery (February to April 2016), bringing together recent projection works by Victor Burgin and a selection of drawings by Roland Barthes rarely seen outside of France. The exhibition played with Barthes’ use of the slash as established in semiology (and notably used in the title of Barthes’ key poststructuralist work S/Z).Key FeaturesPublished as the official catalogue of the exhibition of the same name that is being held at the John Hansard Gallery in Southampton, as well as a stand-alone art and philosophy bookOver 20 full-colour illustrations, including newly commissioned work by Victor Burgin and images of Barthes’ work on paperContains newly commissioned text by Victor Burgin and unpublished conversations with him on his recent projection works and their theoretical implications  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDrawingxExhibitionsx21st century. 0aDrawingy21st centuryvExhibitions. 0aPhotography, ArtisticxExhibitionsx21st centuryxExhibition catalogsxInterviewsxExhibition catalogsxExhibition catalogs. 0aPhotography, Artisticy21st centuryvExhibitions. 4aPhilosophy. 7aART / Individual Artists / General.2bisacsh1 aBishop, Ryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurgin, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoster, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManghani, Sunil, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aManghani, Sunil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311078044440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147441554540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474415545423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com